    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="250"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Executive Agreement Series No. 38</note>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.6227/21</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The German Under Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs
                            (<persName corresp="#p_BBW1" type="from">Von Bülow</persName>) to the
                        American Ambassador in Germany (<persName corresp="#p_SFM1" type="to"
                            >Sackett</persName>)</hi>
                    <note n="87" xml:id="d250fn87">Transmitted to the Department by the Ambassador
                        as an enclosure to his despatch No. 1764, May 31, 1932; received June
                        14.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">II F 1269, I</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-30">May 30,
                            1932</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of Your Excellency’s two communications of May 27—Nos. 797 and 798<note
                        n="88" xml:id="d250fn88">For No. 798 and the arrangement relating to
                        certificates of airworthiness for imported aircraft, see <ref
                            target="#pg_349">pp. 349</ref> ff.</note>—and to state that the text
                    given therein of the Arrangements between Germany and the United States of
                    America governing air traffic and the reciprocal acceptance of certificates of
                    airworthiness for aircraft imported from the other country as merchandise, meets
                    with the approval of the German Government. There is agreement in opinion that
                    the two Arrangements shall go into effect on June 1, 1932.</p>
                <p>I avail myself [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BBW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">B. W. von Bülow</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
